  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db9\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd \u0da2\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dc1\u0dba\u0dda \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Steps to remove dead elk from Ambewela Reservoir",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Samantha Jayasundara, Assistant Superintendent of Police of Nuwara Eliya Police Division, said that necessary measures will be taken to remove the bodies of a large number of dead elk in Ambewela Reservoir, Nuwara Eliya.",
        "A group of officers of the Nuwara Eliya Police, including the Assistant Superintendent of Police, conducted an investigation at the reservoir today (24th) following a notification by the Station Commander of the Ambewela Police Station that a large number of elks had died in the reservoir.",
        "After the inquiry, the Assistant Superintendent of Police said that elk hunters roaming in the Horton plains ecological zone and Ambewela reserve are caught in the traps set and the elk coming to Ambewela reserve in search of food and water in the reserve are bitten by the roaming hunting dogs and the elk are chased into the reservoir.",
        "After being bitten by the hunting dogs, the elk's scars are not visible, and after that the elk that jump to save their lives in the reservoir drown in the reservoir and die.",
        "The Dhiwaras who are engaged in the Dhiwara industry in that reservoir also claim that Ambewela Reservoir has a special place among the cleanest reservoirs in the Nuwara Eliya district.",
        "It is said that some people in the reservoir which is 996 acres are engaged in the dhiwara industry, and due to the death of a large number of elks in the reservoir in a short period of two months, a situation has arisen where it is impossible to engage in the dhiwara industry.",
        "Dhivareen claims that there are about 30 stray hunting dogs roaming in the Ambewela reserve, and those dogs live by hunting animals like elk, deer, rabbits, and anyone who enters the reserve can see the dogs.",
        "Although the wildlife officers were informed about this, they came to the place and conducted an investigation, but there has been no response so far. A group of public health inspectors came and cut off the head of a dead elephant to find out if the dead elephant was infected with hydrops. Dhivarin said."
      ],
